						               													<description>Make Your Words Count! Game&amp;#10;Object of the Game: To be the first player to 100 points/high score by using the cards in hand (5 or 7 cards dealt) to make words.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to Play: Choose a dealer.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Community Vowel cards (A, E, I, O, U) will be laid out by the dealer on the playing board. &amp;#10;    Each Community Vowel can be used once per round when making words. &amp;#10;    Dealer will then shuffle remaining cards &amp;amp; deal 5 or 7 cards to each player to make their best word. &amp;#10;    After dealing cards to each player, the remaining cards will be placed faced down in a pile to pick from each round. &amp;#10;    Each round, players will make their own words by using the cards in their hand and/or Community Vowels on the playing board. &amp;#10;    Each player will display their created words to earn points based on value of each card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Keep track of the scores. For example, if you have the letters W, R, D, S &amp;amp; T in hand &amp;amp; the Community Vowels are A, E, I, O and U, you can make W O R D S from the letters in hand and O from the Community Vowels. Since W = 4, O = 0 (Community Vowel), R = 1, D = 2 and S = 1, the point total equals 8 (i.e. 4+1+2+1) for the round. Each player will have 30 seconds to make a word each round. &amp;#10;    For the next round, pick up the number of cards used from the pile. &amp;#10;    You can discard up to two cards per round (can still play the round). &amp;#10;    Use all cards in hand = 20 more points!&amp;#10;    Go to alphaearlapps.com for word lists. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
